ce:section.ce:para:
The experimental process can be divided into four distinct stages.

                              Ⅰ.

Passive heating stage: Commencing with the initiation of heating and extending until the moment when the safety valve ruptures;


                              Ⅱ.

Self-accelerating reaction stage: From the initiation of combustion in the hot flue gas until the completion of pre-combustion;


                              Ⅲ.

Extinguishing stage: Commencing with the initiation of extinguishing agent deployment and concluding upon its termination;


                              Ⅳ.

Submerged cooling stage: Subsequent to the completion of extinguishing agent discharge, the LFP will be fully enveloped by the CNF and subjected to continuous cooling.
